lf features a solo recital by Swagatalakshmi Dasgupta.				 																WORKSHOP				 																																	 July 7 - 10 at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake; 10 am - 5 pm: EZCC holds Nritta Nathuvangam  a workshop on the aesthetics and mathematics of rhythm in Bharata Natyam, to be conducted by Prakriti Bhaskar of Mumbai. Details at 6796.				 																TALK				 																																	 July 7 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 5 pm: Sitanath Goswami will speak in Bengali on Panchadashi.				 																																	 July 7 at Ramakrishna Vedanta Math, 19A amp; B Raja Rajkrishna Street; 7 pm: Swami Buddhatmanada will speak in Bengali on Sri Ramakrishna Kathamrita.				 																																	 July 7 at Ramakrishna Mission Saradapitha, Belur Math; 6 pm: Swami Shastrajnananda will speak on Vivek Chudamoni				 																VARIETY				 																																	 Till July 7 at Oxford Bookstore, Park Street; 6.30 pm: In keeping with bicentenary celebrations of George Sand, Alliance Francaise de Calcutta, Les Promthens and Oxford Bookstore present George Sand, Ras Sundari Debi and Noti Binodini  A Study of Contexts. Besides a day-long exhibition, the concluding session (at 6.30 pm) features a panel discussion (Topic: Women, Work, Family: Women as Creator; Panelists: Chinmoy Guha, Samik Bandyopadhyay, Rajat Kanta Roy and Samita Sen; Moderator: Subhas Ranjan Chakraborty).				 																FASHION				 																																	 July 7 at Shoppers Stop, Salt Lake; 3 pm: Bhaichung Bhutia launches the Men in Vogue Promotion based on the theme, fashion meets fortune. The promotion is on from July 8 -25 at both Elgin Road and Salt Lake stores.
